---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import SchemeRepl from '../../../../components/SchemeRepl';
---

<Layout title="Scheme in 5 Minutes" favicon="🟢">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to reading list</a>

    <h1>Scheme in 5 Minutes</h1>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Everything is an expression. Parentheses are function calls. That's it.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: anatomy of a Scheme expression -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 320 100" class="w-full max-w-sm" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- The expression -->
        <text x="160" y="35" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="18">(  <tspan fill="#60a5fa">+</tspan>   <tspan fill="#34d399">3</tspan>   <tspan fill="#34d399">4</tspan>  )</text>
        <!-- Annotation arrows -->
        <line x1="120" y1="45" x2="120" y2="65" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <text x="120" y="78" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="9">operator</text>
        <line x1="170" y1="45" x2="170" y2="60" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <line x1="200" y1="45" x2="200" y2="60" stroke="#34d399" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <text x="185" y="78" text-anchor="middle" fill="#34d399" font-size="9">operands</text>
        <!-- Result -->
        <text x="270" y="35" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="14" fill-opacity="0.4">=  7</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Expressions -->
    <h3>Expressions</h3>
    <p>Every Scheme program is an expression. An expression in parentheses calls a function: the first element is the function, the rest are arguments. Nesting works the way you'd expect.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`(+ 1 2)
`} />

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`(* 3 4)
`} />

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Nesting: (2 * 3) + 1
(+ (* 2 3) 1)
`} />

    <!-- 2. Define -->
    <h3>Define</h3>
    <p>Use <code>define</code> to bind a name to a value or to define a function.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`(define x 5)
(display x)
`} />

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`(define (square x) (* x x))

(display (square 5))
`} />

    <!-- 3. Lists -->
    <h3>Lists</h3>
    <p>Lists are the core data structure. Quote a list with <code>'</code> to prevent evaluation. <code>car</code> returns the first element, <code>cdr</code> returns the rest, <code>cons</code> adds an element to the front.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`(display '(1 2 3)) (newline)

(display (car '(1 2 3))) (newline)

(display (cdr '(1 2 3))) (newline)

(display (cons 0 '(1 2 3)))
`} />

    <!-- 4. Conditionals -->
    <h3>Conditionals</h3>
    <p><code>if</code> takes a test, a then-branch, and an else-branch. <code>cond</code> handles multiple branches.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`(display (if (> 3 2) 'yes 'no))
`} />

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`(define (classify n)
  (cond
    ((< n 0) 'negative)
    ((= n 0) 'zero)
    (else 'positive)))

(display (classify -1)) (newline)
(display (classify 0)) (newline)
(display (classify 7))
`} />

    <!-- 5. Higher-order functions -->
    <h3>Higher-order functions</h3>
    <p>Functions that take other functions as arguments. <code>map</code> applies a function to every element. <code>filter</code> keeps elements that pass a test.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`(define (square x) (* x x))

(display (map square '(1 2 3))) (newline)

(display (filter odd? '(1 2 3 4 5)))
`} />

    <!-- 6. Lambda -->
    <h3>Lambda</h3>
    <p><code>lambda</code> creates an anonymous function. You can pass it directly without naming it first.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; A lambda that squares its argument
(display ((lambda (x) (* x x)) 4)) (newline)

; Passing a lambda to map
(display (map (lambda (x) (+ x 10)) '(1 2 3)))
`} />

    <!-- 7. Let -->
    <h3>Let</h3>
    <p><code>let</code> creates local bindings. Each binding is a name-value pair. The bindings are only visible inside the body.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`(let ((x 3) (y 4))
  (display (+ x y)))
`} />

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-center text-sm text-gray-400 mt-10">
      That's enough to read every page on this site.
    </div>

  </main>
</Layout>
